Client sandbox of GigaBio LLC. Everything in this folder is drafted for GigaBio and only for GigaBio — see the firm's cross-client leakage prohibition. Note: GigaBio's positions are deliberately the opposite of other clients of the firm; never let another client's "friendlier" terms bleed into GigaBio documents.

# matter GigaBio Research Protection {#gigabio_matter}

Pearson Specter Litt LLP protects the research programme of GigaBio LLC, a biotechnology company whose entire value is its compound library, assay data, and the synthesis know-how of its researchers. GigaBio's standing instruction: lock down IP and personnel as hard as the law allows — it would rather lose a hire than leak a molecule.

# party GigaBio {#gigabio_party}

GigaBio LLC, a limited liability company incorporated in England and Wales with company number 09182736, with its registered office at 4 Crick Lane, Cambridge CB2 1TN, United Kingdom ("**GigaBio**").

# jurisdiction England and Wales {#gigabio_law}

All GigaBio documents are governed by the laws of England and Wales. UK statutory regimes apply as mandatory law. Flag any requested provision an English court would not enforce — particularly restraints of trade — instead of silently drafting or silently dropping it.

# fact GigaBio Profile {#gigabio_facts}

- GigaBio researches small-molecule therapeutics targeting metabolic and muscle-wasting conditions.
- Its principal asset is a proprietary compound library and the associated assay data.
- Research staff are a mix of employees and independent contractor researchers.

# definition Restricted Field {#gigabio_def_field}

"**Restricted Field**" means research, development, or commercialization of small-molecule compounds targeting the biological pathways on which the relevant individual worked for GigaBio, as recorded in the project records for their engagement.

# redline Exclusive Rights Only {#gigabio_redline_exclusive}

All intellectual property created in the course of any engagement for GigaBio is assigned to GigaBio outright. Non-exclusive rights to engagement IP are never acceptable, in any document, for any counterparty.

## fallback Exclusive Licence

Only where assignment is legally impossible for a specific category of rights: an exclusive, perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free, sublicensable licence to GigaBio, with a covenant not to license or exploit the rights for anyone else. This is the only fallback — there is no second position.

# redline Hard Three-Year Non-Compete {#gigabio_redline_noncompete}

Every research engagement — employee or contractor — includes a post-termination non-compete in the Restricted Field of exactly three (3) years. The duration is never shortened, and the covenant is never softened into a mere non-solicitation or confidentiality duty.

## fallback Scope Narrowing

If enforceability under the English restraint-of-trade doctrine demands narrowing, narrow the Restricted Field definition or the territory for that document — never the three-year duration. Record the narrowing and its reason in the report.

# style GigaBio Voice {#gigabio_style}

UK English spelling throughout ("licence" as noun, "programme", "organisation"). Formal register; precision over brevity.
